# Design Patterns

This project implements **4 Design Patterns** from the Gang of Four (GoF) catalogue.

---

## Pattern 1 — Factory Method 

### Category
Creational Pattern

### Intent
Define an interface for creating objects, but let the factory decide which class to instantiate. The client never calls `new` directly.

### Problem it Solves
UNO has 3 types of cards: `NumberCard`, `ActionCard`, and `WildCard`. Without a factory, every part of the code that creates cards must know which class to instantiate and how. If we add a new card type, we must find and update every place that creates cards.

### Solution
`CardFactory` is the single place responsible for all card creation.

```
CardFactory
├── createNumberCard(color, value)  → NumberCard
├── createActionCard(color, type)  → ActionCard
├── createWildCard(type)           → WildCard
└── createFullDeck()               → List<Card> (108 cards, shuffled)
```

### Code
```java
// CardFactory.java
public class CardFactory {

    public static Card createNumberCard(String color, int value) {
        return new NumberCard(color, value);
    }

    public static Card createActionCard(String color, String type) {
        return new ActionCard(color, type);
    }

    public static Card createWildCard(String type) {
        return new WildCard(type);
    }

    public static List<Card> createFullDeck() {
        List<Card> deck = new ArrayList<>();
        for (String color : COLORS) {
            deck.add(createNumberCard(color, 0));
            for (int v = 1; v <= 9; v++) {
                deck.add(createNumberCard(color, v));
                deck.add(createNumberCard(color, v));
            }
            for (String action : new String[]{"SKIP","REVERSE","DRAW_TWO"}) {
                deck.add(createActionCard(color, action));
                deck.add(createActionCard(color, action));
            }
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
            deck.add(createWildCard("WILD"));
            deck.add(createWildCard("WILD_DRAW_FOUR"));
        }
        Collections.shuffle(deck);
        return deck;
    }
}
```

### Roles
| Role | Class |
|------|-------|
| Creator (Factory) | `CardFactory` |
| Product (Abstract) | `Card` |
| Concrete Product | `NumberCard`, `ActionCard`, `WildCard` |

### Benefit
Adding a new card type (e.g., `SwapHandsCard`) only requires one new class + one new factory method. Nothing else changes.

