## Pattern 2 — Observer 

### Category
Behavioural Pattern

### Intent
Define a one-to-many dependency so that when one object (Subject) changes state, all dependents (Observers) are notified automatically.

### Problem it Solves
The game engine needs to log moves, track scores, and potentially update a GUI — but these are separate concerns. Mixing them into `UnoGame` would make it bloated and hard to maintain.

### Solution
`GameEventManager` (Subject) fires events. Any class implementing `GameObserver` receives those events automatically.

```
GameEventManager (Subject)
│
├── notifyCardPlayed()  ──► TurnLogger.onCardPlayed()
├── notifyCardDrawn()   ──► TurnLogger.onCardDrawn()
├── notifyTurnChanged() ──► TurnLogger.onTurnChanged()
├── notifyUnoCallout()  ──► TurnLogger.onUnoCallout()
└── notifyGameEnd()     ──► TurnLogger.onGameEnd()
                        ──► ScoreTracker.onGameEnd()
```

### Code
```java
// GameObserver.java (Observer interface)
public interface GameObserver {
    void onCardPlayed(Player player, Card card);
    void onCardDrawn(Player player, int count);
    void onTurnChanged(Player nextPlayer);
    void onUnoCallout(Player caller, Player target);
    void onGameEnd(Player winner);
}

// TurnLogger.java (Concrete Observer)
public class TurnLogger implements GameObserver {
    @Override
    public void onCardPlayed(Player player, Card card) {
        System.out.println("[LOG] " + player.getName() + " played " + card);
    }
    // ... other events
}

// UnoGame.java (registers observers and fires events)
eventManager.addObserver(new TurnLogger());
eventManager.addObserver(new ScoreTracker());

// Later in game loop:
eventManager.notifyCardPlayed(current, played); // both observers notified
```

### Roles
| Role | Class |
|------|-------|
| Subject | `GameEventManager` |
| Observer Interface | `GameObserver` |
| Concrete Observer | `TurnLogger`, `ScoreTracker` |

### Benefit
Adding a new observer (e.g., a GUI update, a sound player) only requires one new class implementing `GameObserver` and one `addObserver()` call. The game engine never changes.

