## Pattern 3 — Strategy 

### Category
Behavioural Pattern

### Intent
Define a family of algorithms, encapsulate each one, and make them interchangeable. The Strategy lets the algorithm vary independently from the clients that use it.

### Problem it Solves
Different AI players need different play behaviors (Aggressive, Defensive, Random). Without Strategy, this requires `if/else` chains inside `AIPlayer` — messy and hard to extend.

### Solution
`PlayStrategy` is an interface. Each difficulty is a separate class. `AIPlayer` holds a reference and delegates to it.

```
PlayStrategy (interface)
├── AggressiveStrategy  → prefers SKIP, DRAW_TWO, WILD_DRAW_FOUR
├── DefensiveStrategy   → prefers number cards, saves wilds for last
└── RandomStrategy      → picks any playable card at random
```

### Code
```java
// PlayStrategy.java (Strategy interface)
public interface PlayStrategy {
    Card chooseCard(List<Card> playableCards, GameState state);
}

// AggressiveStrategy.java (Concrete Strategy)
public class AggressiveStrategy implements PlayStrategy {
    @Override
    public Card chooseCard(List<Card> playable, GameState state) {
        for (Card c : playable)
            if (c.getType().contains("DRAW")) return c;  // prefer draw cards
        for (Card c : playable)
            if (c.getType().equals("SKIP")) return c;    // then skip
        return playable.get(0);
    }
}

// AIPlayer.java (Context)
public class AIPlayer extends Player {
    private PlayStrategy strategy;  // holds reference to strategy

    public Card takeTurn(GameState state) {
        Card chosen = strategy.chooseCard(getPlayableCards(...), state);
        // ...
    }

    // Strategy can be swapped at runtime!
    public void setStrategy(PlayStrategy strategy) {
        this.strategy = strategy;
    }
}
```

### Roles
| Role | Class |
|------|-------|
| Strategy Interface | `PlayStrategy` |
| Concrete Strategy | `AggressiveStrategy`, `DefensiveStrategy`, `RandomStrategy` |
| Context | `AIPlayer` |

### Benefit
Adding a new AI difficulty only requires one new class implementing `PlayStrategy`. No changes to `AIPlayer` or `UnoGame`.

